# <Process name> — Standard Operating Procedure

An **optional starter** for the deliverable of a `documentation`-kind project (see `### Project kind` in `workflow/project-kind.md`) — a human process / SOP with no executable code. Copy it into `deliverable/` as a seed when the deliverable *is* an SOP / runbook; it is one documentation shape among many, never a mandated scaffold. Written for the operator and read by agents before planning any change to the process.

> Operator **experience flow** lives in `docs/user-journeys.md` (what the person does / expects / what can go wrong) — this SOP is **additive**, not a replacement: a journey references, the SOP specifies. The **good-outcome bar** lives in the feature's Product Contract (Must work / Must not break / Acceptance checks); this SOP's `## Inputs and outputs` and its dry-run acceptance map onto that bar. Any status enumeration / identifier grammar a step would name lives **once** in `docs/architecture.md` `## Behavioral contract (taxonomies & invariants)` and is referenced here, never restated.
