> **Section-set methodology — confirm against primary sources.** The sections below follow standard SOP methodology (BPMN process modelling, ISO 9001 documented information, SIPOC, RACI, Toyota standard work). Treat the exact set as design guidance to confirm against the primary references your domain cites, not as verified fact.
>
> Scale ceremony to the stakes (the `### Project kind` proportionality note): a high-stakes, repeated, multi-role process earns every section; a low-stakes one-off marks the sections that do not apply `N/A — <reason>` rather than deleting them. As a starter, the section set is a starting point, not a contract — keep what fits, drop what does not.

